        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued May 17 at 10:52PM CDT by NWS Tulsa OK</headline>
        <description>At 1052 PM CDT, Doppler radar indicated a strong thunderstorm 8 miles
northwest of Paden, moving east at 35 mph.

HAZARD...Nickel size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Minor hail damage to vegetation is possible.

Locations in or near the path include...
Paden...                          Welty...
Mason...                          Slick...
Okfuskee...
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

A Severe Thunderstorm Watch remains in effect until 400 AM CDT for
northeastern and east central Oklahoma.</instruction>
